{"article_id":"1VtT8AyviVnGyEVk","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The State Department announced Friday","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that it will not release 22 emails from former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"because they contain `` top secret '' information , the highest level of government classification .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"The decision ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"coming three days before the Iowa caucuses ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"could provide fodder for Clinton 's political opponents , especially Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"who are likely to make note of the emails ' `` top secret '' designation .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Clinton 's email use has haunted her on the campaign trail","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"since it became public early last year that she maintained a private server","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"while leading the State Department .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"State Department spokesman John Kirby said","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"the documents ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"totaling 37 pages ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"were not marked classified at the time","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"they were sent ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"but are being upgraded at the request of the Intelligence Community","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"because they contain sensitive information .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"But ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"Kirby said ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"a separate review by the bureaus of Diplomatic Security and Intelligence and Research is being held","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"into whether the information in the emails was classified at the time","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"they were sent and received .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"He would not say","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"when the review began or how long it would go ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"and acknowledged","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"it 's possible there could be classified emails","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"that were n't marked as such .","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"`` It 's certainly possible that for any number of reasons , traffic can be sent","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"that 's not marked appropriately for its classification .","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"That is certainly possible , ''","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"Kirby said .","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"But he added","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"that he was n't going to make any judgments about this particular case .","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"`` All","depth":15},{"id":35,"text":"I can tell you definitively","depth":15},{"id":36,"text":"is it was n't marked classified at the time","depth":15},{"id":37,"text":"it was sent , ''","depth":15},{"id":38,"text":"Kirby said .","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"A senior State Department official said","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"the review `` began very recently ''","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"and was initiated by the State Department ,","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"but the official would n't say","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"what prompted it .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"A spokesperson for the Intelligence Community 's inspector general declined to comment .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Kirby also said","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"18 emails ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"comprised of eight email chains between Clinton and President Barack Obama ,","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"are being `` withheld in full ''","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"to `` protect the President 's ability","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"to receive unvarnished advice and counsel . ''","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"But ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"Kirby said ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"they `` have not been determined to be classified ''","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"and said","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"they will `` ultimately be released in accordance with the Presidential records act . ''","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"Clinton did not mention the email controversy during campaign events Friday .","depth":5},{"id":57,"text":"But in an interview with KCRG in Dubuque , Iowa , Clinton maintained","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"that she `` never emailed anything","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"that was considered to be classified ''","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"and asked for the emails to be released .","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"`` I 'd love for people to see what I did","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"and I hope","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"that will happen , ''","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"she said .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Brian Fallon , a spokesman for Clinton 's campaign , said in a statement","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"that Friday 's announcement was a case of `` over-classification run amok ''","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"and reiterated Clinton 's position","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"that the emails be made public .","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"But later Friday , Fallon declined to say","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"whether Clinton would ask Obama to declassify the emails","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"when pressed by CNN 's Wolf Blitzer on `` The Situation Room .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"'' `` The President easily could declassify all of these emails","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"if she asked him","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"and if he agreed ,","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"right ? ''","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Blitzer asked .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"`` I 'd really be surprised","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"if this has risen to the President 's level , ''","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"Fallon replied .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"`` Because , again , this a mundane matter","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"of fulfilling a FOIA request . ''","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"Asked Friday","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"if he had `` certainty and confidence ''","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"that Clinton will not be indicted over the email controversy ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest said","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"any decision","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"to prosecute Clinton","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"would rest with the Justice Department .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"`` That is a decision","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"to be made solely by independent prosecutors , ''","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Earnest said .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"`` But again ,","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"based on what we know from the Department of Justice ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"it does not seem to be headed in that direction . ''","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"The State Department released more than 900 of Clinton 's emails Friday","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"-- 242 of which received classification upgrades :","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"11 to `` secret '' and 209 more to `` confidential , '' along with the 22 emails","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"containing `` top secret '' information --","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"but the release fell well behind the judge-imposed timetable","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"for producing all of her emails .","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"Clinton seeking to confirm with her team","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"that a piece of information ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"which top aide Jake Sullivan described as proof","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"the new Center for Strategic Counterterrorism Communications was doing its job ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"was `` not classified or otherwise inappropriate '' and fit to share with a reporter ;","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"Evidence","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"that Clinton actively lobbied on behalf of the Affordable Care Act","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"-- at one point , she emailed Miguel Rodriguez , then the director of the White House Office of Legislative Affairs ,","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"to inform him","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"she 'd spoken","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"and received a `` yes '' from then-Arkansas Rep. Marion Berry .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"John Podesta , now the chairman of Clinton 's campaign , emailing aide Cheryl Mills","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"to ask","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"if she had a personal email","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"to which he could send a message hours ahead of a meeting with then-chief of staff Rahm Emanuel .","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"Clinton asking ,","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"`` So , can someone sign just my first name ? ''","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"when presented with a farewell letter","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"( written by Huma Abedin )","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"to former Sen. George Mitchell","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"as he prepared to leave after two years as the top U.S. envoy to the Israelis and Palestinians .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"The emails have been publishing over the last eight months more or less in accordance with a schedule","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"set by Judge Rudolph Contreras ,","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"with increasingly large batches uploaded to a State Department website at the end of each month .","depth":6},{"id":125,"text":"This month 's release was supposed to be the final one","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"and include just over 9,000 pages of documents","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"-- the largest number to date .","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"But last Thursday , the State Department filed a motion","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"to extend the final productions until February 29","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"because the department had failed to send more than 7,000 pages of those emails to other government agencies for review ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"only recognizing the mistake earlier this month .","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"That delay was then compounded by a huge snowstorm","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"that shut down the federal government for several days ,","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"according to the State Department 's motion .","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"Several prominent Republicans ,","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"including presidential hopefuls ,","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"quickly condemned Clinton , the Democratic 2016 front-runner , over Friday 's developments .","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"`` The new e-mail release is a disaster for Hillary Clinton .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"At a minimum , how can someone with such bad","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"( judgment )","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"be our next president ? ''","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"GOP front-runner Donald Trump tweeted .","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"The new e-mail release is a disaster for Hillary Clinton .","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"At a minimum , how can someone with such bad judgement be our next president ?","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"January 29 , 2016","depth":5},{"id":148,"text":"Florida Sen. Marco Rubio said","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"Clinton 's email use was a `` disqualifier '' for the White House .","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"`` Hillary Clinton put some of the highest , most sensitive intelligence information on her private server","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"because maybe she thinks","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"she 's above the law , ''","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"Rubio said at a town hall event in Clinton , Iowa .","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"Texas Sen. Ted Cruz told conservative radio host Hugh Hewitt","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"that Clinton 's email controversy would seriously imperil her presidential aspirations .","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"`` We are talking about serious offenses","depth":11},{"id":157,"text":"for which the Obama Justice Department threw the book at General","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"( David )","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"Petraeus , ''","depth":12},{"id":160,"text":"Cruz said .","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"`` And justice needs to be enforced fairly and impartially . ''","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"And Republican National Committee Chairman Reince Priebus tweeted","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"that Clinton and the Obama administration have `` obfuscated and misled at every available opportunity , ''","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"that she has `` removed all doubt","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"that she can not be trusted with the presidency . ''","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"With even more `` top-secret '' emails on her secret server , Clinton has removed all doubt","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"that she can not be trusted with the presidency","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"- Reince Priebus","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"( @ Reince )","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"January 29 , 2016","depth":9},{"id":172,"text":"But Rep. Adam Schiff , D-California , the ranking Democrat on the House Intelligence Committee , said","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"classification determinations `` are often very complex . ''","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"`` It 's important to remember","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"that none of these emails had any classification markings at the time","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"they were sent ,","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"and Secretary Clinton and her staff were responding to world events in real time","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"without the benefit of months of analysis after the fact , ''","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"Schiff said .","depth":8},{"id":180,"text":"Meanwhile , Clinton 's top Democratic 2016 rival , Vermont Sen. Bernie Sanders , said in a statement","depth":8},{"id":181,"text":"that `` there is a legal process in place","depth":9},{"id":182,"text":"which should proceed","depth":10},{"id":183,"text":"and not be politicized . ''","depth":10},{"id":184,"text":"`` The voters of Iowa and this nation deserve a serious discussion of the issues","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"facing them , ''","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"Sanders said ,","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"and referenced the Democratic debate in October ,","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"when he memorably declined to attack Clinton over the issue .","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"`` The American people are sick and tired of hearing about your damn emails , ''","depth":10},{"id":190,"text":"he said then to applause .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":381,"left":0,"right":380,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":380,"left":284,"right":379,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":284,"left":245,"right":283,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":245,"left":200,"right":244,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":197,"right":199,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":193,"right":196,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":193,"left":1,"right":192,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":192,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":194,"right":195,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":194,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":195,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":8,"right":198,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":198,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":206,"right":243,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":206,"left":11,"right":205,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":205,"left":203,"right":204,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":203,"left":201,"right":202,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":201,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":243,"left":232,"right":242,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":232,"left":210,"right":2